for-loop fast ko n aage isliye le jaata hai taaki gap = n ban jaaye
Jab fast end par hota hai, slow delete-target ke just pehle hota hai
Fir slow->next = slow->next->next se node delete ho jaata hai

🔍 n = 2 ka dry run (head = [1,2,3,4,5])
Nodes ko index maan lo:
1(0) → 2(1) → 3(2) → 4(3) → 5(4)
Step A: Gap set karo (n = 2)
Start: slow=1, fast=1
Move fast 2 steps: fast=3, slow=1 (Gap = 2)

⚠️ Special case: n == length (head hi delete karna)
Example: head = [10,20,30], n = 3
Fast ko 3 steps aage le jaoge → fast == NULL ho jaayega
Iska matlab delete karna wala node head hi hai
Toh simply: head = head->next; return kar do

class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* removeNthFromEnd(ListNode* head, int n) {
     ListNode* slow = head;
     ListNode* fast = head;

     for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
        fast = fast->next;
     }
     if(fast == NULL){
        head = head->next;
        return head;
     }
     while(fast ->next != NULL){
        slow = slow->next;
        fast = fast->next;
     }
     ListNode* dle = slow->next;
     slow->next = slow->next->next;
     delete(dle);
     return head;   
    }
};
